  "doc_id": "39272",
  "text": "Clinical CMV isolates for this study were collected at four geographically separate institutions from 40 unrelated subjects who had received organ transplants or had human immunodeficiency virus infection. Some patients had received prior anti-CMV therapy. Susceptibility to ganciclovir and foscarnet was determined by plaque reduction in fibroblast cell culture. The 50% inhibitory drug concentration (IC 50 ) was determined, and an isolate was considered sensitive if the ganciclovir IC 50 was 6 M or less and the foscarnet IC 50 was 400 M or less [CITATION_1] . For the 40 isolates selected, the ganciclovir IC 50 ranged from 0.8 to 5.8 M and the foscarnet IC 50 ranged from 60 to 280 M. All isolates were therefore considered sensitive to both drugs.",
