      "span_text": "Susceptibility to ganciclovir and foscarnet was determined by plaque reduction in fibroblast cell culture. The 50% inhibitory drug concentration (IC 50 ) was determined, and an isolate was considered sensitive if the ganciclovir IC 50 was 6 M or less and the foscarnet IC 50 was 400 M or less [CITATION_1] ."
